One of the great discoveries of my last year’s trip to Eu- rope was the Pear Brandy of Switzerland. | fell in love with the clean, fruity flavor also intrigued by the fact that a giant pear sits quietly in the center of the bot- tle. adding its eye appeal to the fabulous pear flavor. Incidentally, this feat 1s ac- complished by putting a bottle around the pear bud in the Spring. the pear keeps erowing and growing, until it almost fills the bottle — the pear brandy is added, preserving the pear practically forever into the future. The entire crop yielded only 218 bottles of this unique Pear Brandy and J strongly suggest that you reserve some for the most astonishing of Christmas gifts, or for your own holiday pleasure—$14.95—due Dec. 15th.
